HEADWORD: Doggish
<hw>Dog"gish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a dog; having
the bad qualities of a dog; churlish; growling; brutal.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Dog"gish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Dog"gish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>doggoned</ent>⟦br⟧
